  "text": "IL-15 signalling is therefore essential in maintaining body composition and immune function. However, a decline in serum levels of IL-15 and soluble IL-15R α was observed in murine aging models and expression of intramuscular IL-15 and IL-15R α decreases in aged rats [ 8 , 14 ] Substantiating this data, an age-dependent decline in IL-15 serum levels in humans has been reported [CITATION_1] . Although the impact of IL-15 in an aging system is not yet fully understood, IL-15 signalling is implicated in sustaining NK-cells, neutrophils and lymphocyte function in old age.",
